intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of the course students will be able to:
Identify the key concepts and exemplars in the design of novel visualisation systems, collaborative systems, and multimodal systems, and in ethical system design;
Identify the main issues and key concepts in evaluating such systems, in terms of immediate functionality and utility as well as in terms of wider social, legal and ethical criteria;
Have experience designing such systems, by designing, developing and evaluating a significant piece of interactive software embodying key aspects of the course.
